<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you have asked me to stop roleplaying with you, either I have missed the tell/e-mail/post because I do not remember this at all. If you wish for me to stop roleplaying with you, say the words and just like I do with the other one, you are out and we go out seperate ways. I hate doing this because it brings OOC into the reason but I have had to do this once simply because I was stupid and got OOC angry at someone, and it showed up in my roleplay towards this person. I regret doing this everyday that I play this game, but I have moved on, I hope that other person has moved on, and we don't bother eachother. If you would like something like this, post clearly that you would and it will be done.<br>
<br>
But you seem to misunderstand somethings. In no way do I want to break up friendships over my roleplay. <br>
<br>
OOC Alliance. Raiding is apart of roleplay. Just my personal belief, that is all. I beieve it because you are close friends with alot of HoD peoples, its a way that you can raid together and have HoD be looked at by the other Roleplayers as a non evil guild. <br>
<br>
I dont believe in OOC alliances, personally. If you're gonna raid with lighties, just do it. If you are not, then don't. Why is it so important? If you want to be an evil guild, be one. Nakath, why does this have you so angry? So HoD wouldn't raid with EO. Is your friendship with them purely based on raiding together? I know this isn't true, I'm just tossing out questions.<br>
<br>
Nercopolis and my Invatation<br>
If you expected me to Ignore HoD, you were wrong. I would love it for them to break off this OOC alliance, really I would. Nothing against Nakath, really. But I can't comprise my roleplay by letting a Guild that openly raids with lightbringers be a fullmember of the Nercopolis.<br>
<br>
I will not flame anyones RP style and say that they are wrong. Such is not my place. I disagree with OOC raiding alliances. Thats all I'll say about that. If you want to do such, thats your own thing.<br>
<br>
Shintou made Nercopolis to save evil. Part of saving Evil is saving people from joining lightbringer guilds. Shintou saw EO and HoD raiding together alot. Shintou wishes to break HoD from EO. Nothing personal against Nakath. Its all roleplay, and not to be taken personaly.<br>
<br>
In this quest, Shintou has also learned a bit of tolerance. If HoD did not want to break off the alliance, they are still free to come to the Nercopolis, Roleplay. Raid. (Even post their own raids just cannot be an offical Nercopolis raid, but if people in Nercopolis wants to Help HoD, thats their choice) Quest. Buy and Sell (They just can't have sticky 'Shops' set up). Have their characters worship (They just can't lead any churches, or set up one). And they cannot be in our guildwars (As shintou can't trust them, because they are allied with lighties, and shintou is going to be guildwarring against lighties. Again, nothing personal.) And they cannot set up an Embassy. But other then that, they are free to use the Nercopolis as most other evil people will.<br>
If I have implied anything different in any of my posts, then I misspoke. This is what I am saying here and now.<br>
<br>
Nakath, you can call me what you want. Go ahead, curse scream and yell.<br>
<br>
I don't hate you, and I refuse to flame you. You are good peoples. Thats all I have to say.<br>
