<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Those who see people without the RP flag on should assume that the actions of the avatar aren't IC unless they're given reasons to believe otherwise<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I see two significant problems with that proposal.<br>
<br>
Firstly, many people like to keep their class and level OOCly visible, but unfortunately, the /role flag hides said information, which is why a substantial number of roleplayers--myself included--aren't &quot;officially&quot; roleplaying.<br>
<br>
Secondly, what do I do when I want to make an OOC remark in the middle of an IC conversation? Switch the /role flag off, say something OOC, then switch /role back on? I am willing to bet 95% of all players would never even notice you made the status switch.<br>
<br>
If I want to distinguish between IC and OOC actions, I simply enclose anything OOC inside double parentheses, for instance: /gsay (( *smiles* Congratulations on 60th level! )). Most people seem to catch on pretty quickly and react accordingly (assuming they are roleplayers in the first place, mind you.) Of course, the ideal would be differently colored text output depending on a character's /role status plus the option to publicize class and level information while set /role, but the chances of our ever seeing that implemented are slim to none.<br>
<br>
