<br>
I read all of the threads posted on this and every post in the entire story, and all I have to say is....calm down Naketh.  Step back, take a few deep breaths, read a few Calvin and Hobbes...books, and then return to this and think about it objectively.<br>
<br>
It seems PoShintou has absolutely nothing against you.  He seems to simply be attempting to create something equivlant to the good/neutral Fellowship.  And I must say that it is a very difficult task.  It isn't difficult getting the numbers together, but what is really hard is getting the rules in place and getting the players to abide by them.<br>
<br>
In the Fellowship, we have some very specific rules with regards to darkies.  First, no guild in the Fellowship has a single dark elf, troll, ogre, iksar, necromancer, or shadowknight.  No Fellowship event allows outside evils (as defined above) to come unless the leader of the event specifically warns the attendees of their presence...in which case, I know of a large list of regular Fellowship raiders who would refuse to attend.  <br>
<br>
The debate that I referred to on this is the question, &quot;well, what if the dark elf role-plays as a good person?&quot;  I'd say this debate comes up at least once every three months.  The result is always the same.  We follow the race/class definitions of evil provided by sony.<br>
<br>
Why?  There are many rationales, but the one which makes the most sense to me is the fact that there are enough characters in the Fellowship who refuse to see these races and professions as anything but evil.  Drizzt would die if he came to the Fellowship halls...unless Meledi could invis and sneek him out fast enough.<br>
<br>
Of course, we can still do whatever we want in our time that we are not doing something with the Fellowship within the rules of our individual guilds.  I can group with an evil if I feel so inclined without any repercussions...except perhaps having people look at me differently IC if my group happens to run across a fellowship group.<br>
<br>
In any case, it seems to me that Shintou is trying to forge alliances in the same manner that the Fellowship has them.  Set up some rules, open a chat, have a board, and have fun.  I'm sorry if you can't participate because you don't fit his criteria, but he was just giving the Harvesters the option to join.  He was not requiring them to do so.  And you can still do whatever you want.<br>
<br>
If the alliance is OOC, then perhaps denial would be the best route.  (and I did see that someone...I'm terrible with names...did choose that route)  Just deny IC that you ever had dealings with the other guild.  If he saw your guilds grouping together, I'm sure there is some kind of IC excuse that could be baked up.<br>
