<br>
HoD has an OOC alliance with EO.<br>
<br>
I had thought that this was for good vs evil type rps and stuff.  The way I am taking it now is that HoD is evil only but when they don't feel like RPing they group with this good guild.<br>
<br>
If that is incorrect let me know.<br>
<br>
Now I pose the question how the more harcore RPer like Shin or myself are supposed to take this. <br>
 <br>
When we are IC and we approach an ally or fellow darksoul that we have hunted with and they are frolicing with a pale, what are we supposed to do?<br>
<br>
A) Turn off our RP because they chosen to and do the same?<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
B) React IC and get the type of response seen at the top of this thread.<br>
<br>
Neither is really a great choice.  I think Shintou is trying to avoid this type of thing in what he is trying to build. <br>
<br>
Shin basically said,<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey I have a thing I am trying to do that will be great for RP in the evil community.  It will create some great RP and help the community gain greater depth than it has had previously.<br>
<br>
HoD you are one of the guilds I would like to participate, however the feeling of community will be weakend if people are not sure if you are in an RP mood or if you are OOC.  As such if you want to participate this would need to be rectified.  It's your choice, do with it as you will.&quot;<br>
<br>
That is my basic interpetation of all this....is it correct?<br>
<br>
If so then I don't really see where Shintou acted poorly in any way.  He was trying to include people in something for fun.  Things like this have to have guidelines.  If you didn't like the proposal then just say no...what is the problem? <br>
<br>
Fajon<br>
