How do we know this is ooc information?  There are several ambassodors for Necropolis that could have passed the information on to the him.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofshadows.net/sigs/Poyson.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eveningshadow>EveningShadow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 419<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/03 11:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3602.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shintou</span><hr size=1> Saying that its out-of-character isnt exactly right.  I mean it may be OOC in the minds of those that do it, and thats fine, but... I dunno, it just doesnt seem right.  It's like you telling ME what my character sees and how he can react.  As stated many many times before, thats a big no-no.<br>
<br>
It's like only calling things OOC when it suits you.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Well, my character is &quot;evil&quot; and therefore should be treated as such, but heavens no Im not going to disadvantage myself in any way, shape, or form!  I want the best of ALL worlds, and damn you for trying to bring it IC.&quot;<br>
<br>
It's like playing for the Bengals and being pissed when you cant get into the Browns after-game Win party.<br>
<br>
I think its important to note, however, that there is nothing wrong with someone deciding to do this... play both sides.  I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> personally </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> dont like it, and wont do it myself... but Ive no control over anyone's game but my own.  However, as someone who spends a lot of time in the Necropolis site and channel, I want to see it be supportive of those that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> do </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> choose to take the harder road and remain completly IC with their interactions.  <br>
<br>
I will be frank and say that, as a totally IC player, I need help from other IC evils.  I just cant efficently solo anymore (honestly, I never could...)  Because of the character choices I make, it does put me at a disadvantage, and in a real rock-meets-hardplace situation.  Its no fun to sit LFG in Knowledge or Tranq for hours, but its also no fun to just grind exp and not RP my character properly.  Both suck pretty equally.<br>
<br>
To me, the entire necropolis thing comes down to a place where we can soften that disadvantage a bit and help each other.  If you've already made that choice to ignore a portion of your characters roleplay (for good or bad, that's not my judgement to make,) then why make a fuss over someone suggesting you be barred from the place?<br>
<br>
In fact, that's not EVEN what was proposed.  All that was stated, from what I can tell, is that a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> GUILD </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that choose such actions would not have an official embassy on the IC portion of the board.  No one said (as far as I can tell) that individual members couldnt take advantage of the board, the channel or the contacts.<br>
<br>
So, I fail to see the reason for hostility?<br>
<br>
I dont agree with ignoring RP for convience.  I do talk with plenty of people OOC and am a very social and, I think, friendly person.  I live with the choices I make for my character, and the difficulties it causes.  Many others reap the tangible advantages (loot, exp, coin) from not roleplaying.  There are disadvantages to everything, and as much as we would like it, we cant always get everything we want.  <br>
<br>
Being excluded from something sucks, and the knee-jerk reaction is often to lash out, but being a part of A, often time excludes you from B. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~Vabris Vy'Tok, Patron of House Vy'Tok~<br>
